how do i snap out of this funk during pregnancy i am thankful and feel blessed that we finally got pregnant i'm weeks along but i've been having a hard time emotionally i've been going through periods where everything hurts my feelings everything makes me mad all i want to do is crawl into bed a cry my eyes out what is my problem and how do i snap out of it i know it's hormones but i need a break from this emotional roller coaster please serious suggestions only you should talk to your husband about how you're feeling maybe the two of you can go away for the weekend and spend some time together if it makes you feel better make it a no baby weekend don't talk or even think about the baby for the whole weekend or if it makes you feel better go shopping for the baby and buy the outfit to bring the baby home in or something for the nursery if you can't afford to go away for the weekend spend the weekend at home with your husband just try to stay busy to take your mind off of everything i know it's hard i'm pregnant as well at the beginning of my pregnancy i cried because my husband forgot to get me sweet and sour sauce for my chicken nuggets at mcdonalds EastEnders Breastfeeding Friends Knots Landing Jon Secada Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Sex and the City Neighbours Humphrey Bogart Shaggy dog story Ron and Fez Jam (TV series) Melanie Wilkes Kodocha Guinea pig Everwood The Smoking Room Miscarriage One Life to Live Hollyoaks Childbirth Emotions (album) Social rule Postpartum depression Street-Legal Phoebe Buffay's songs The Beatles discography Marie Antoinette Boston Public Nuggets: Original Artyfacts from the First Psychedelic Era, 1965-1968 Princess Marie-Th__r__se-Charlotte The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Egg (food) Obstetrics Johnny Cash Sharon Tate Prostate cancer Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Days of our Lives Roller coaster Abortion debate Ty Cobb T'Pol Cindy Sheehan Hip hop collaborations About a Boy I Don't Wan